Using the aws_vpc_security_group_ingress_rule resource type, perform the following:
Read the sg.csv file using appropriate Terraform functions
Create ingress rules only — ignore all rows where direction = out
The cidr_block column value in CSV determines which subnet CIDR to use as cidr_ipv4 for the rule, based on the following mapping:

cidr_block value	cidr_ipv4 to use

app	CIDR block of app-subnet
database	CIDR block of database-subnet
monitoring	CIDR block of central-subnet
anti-virus	CIDR block of central-subnet

Use the source column as the Security Group to associate the rule with
Handle port ranges (e.g., 8080-8082) by correctly splitting into from_port and to_port
Tag each rule with the ticket column value using a tag named ticket
Use for_each to create all rules dynamically — do not create individual resource blocks per rule  



